casebody.data:
George Green v. The State. No. 8914. Decided October 29, 1924.

No motion for rehearing filed.

No biref filed by appellant. Tom Garrard, State’s Attorney, and Grover C. Morris, Assistant State’s Attorney, for the State. MORROW, Presiding Judge.

— The offense is forgery; punishment fixed at confinement in the penitentiary for a period of two years.

The facts heard by the trial court are not before us. No fault in the procedure is complained of by bill of exceptions or perceived by this court.

The judgment is affirmed.

Affirmed.
